com.camerontec.util.datamodel

Interface IndexedBytesFieldImporter

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Message
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IndexedArrayOfFields, MessageImpl, NullMessage

    public interface IndexedBytesFieldImporter
    Interface to be implemented by classes capable of importing fields whose values are represented as byte arrays.

    Implementations may optionally support the concept of field hierarchy. If they do then the following concepts apply:

    • The root field group is at depth 0.
    • Each field has exactly one parent field.
    • The depth of a child field is equal to the depth of its parent field + 1.
    • Child fields are conceptually organised into field groups.

      • importBytesFieldAtDepth

        int importBytesFieldAtDepth(int depth,
                            int parentIndex,
                            boolean firstInGroup,
                            int key,
                            int valueOffset,
                            int valueLength)
        Import a byte array field at a specified depth as a child of the specified parent field.
        Parameters:
        depth - The import depth. A value ≤ 0 represents the root group.
        parentIndex - The index of the field's parent field. This must be the result of a previous call to importBytesField(int, int, int) or importBytesFieldAtDepth(int, int, boolean, int, int, int), which implies that it is not possible to import a field before its parent.
        firstInGroup - True if this is the first field in a field group.
        key - The key.
        valueOffset - The value offset.
        valueLength - The value length.
        Returns:
        The index at which the field was imported.
